{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/none/microfrontend/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Labidi Aymen"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"f06b9f7a-a50e-51a2-9ed0-83f18fde6d37","excerpt":"","html":"<!-- ---\r\ntitle: \"The era of the Microfrontend\"\r\nauthor: \"Aymen\"\r\ndate: \"2022-06-21\"\r\ncategories:\r\n  - javascript\r\n  - angular\r\ntags: \"\"\r\ncover: ../images/microfrontend.jpeg\r\n---\r\n\r\n##\r\n\r\nBack in 1997 Internet explorer introduced Iframe to integrate webpage inside an other.\r\nIn this case we can have a parent application that call a second party application with only the url.\r\n\r\nThis feature has been explored widly in the entrepise apllication, which provided a good way the build application on top of each other.\r\n\r\nAfter the rise of the frontend Framework, single page application become (SPA) become so populaire, which force the search engines the render the webpage to extract the SEO tags.\r\n\r\nYears later we start having a wide range of frontend frameworks some of them are deprecated.\r\n\r\nThe problematiqe that re-writing exsiting code is painfull, keeping the code up to date is even more painfull.\r\n\r\nIn the other hands some framework are more powerfull in some features more than others.\r\n\r\nBefore the rise of the microfrontend, the microservices has been taken palce in the backend which give more flexibilty on the technologies used in the backend and handling the perfermonce and the high availablities.\r\n\r\nLong short story: the microfrontnend is the same principle but in the frontend.\r\n\r\n## Open the door for multi-Framework frontend\r\n\r\nWhen we start writing frontend many libreraies start to popup to make the developer life easer and add more productibiy, jQuery as example.\r\n\r\nThen we start having MVVM Framework offring two-way binding.\r\n\r\nAfter writing a complete application with one framework there's no way to start using an other.\r\n\r\nWith Miscrofrontned two or more Framework can co-exist in the same application.\r\n\r\nLet's take an example:\r\n\r\nWe start building an Entreprise applcation and the Frontend Architect choose Angular Framework as the main Framework.\r\nBut after starting te project we found React Librery is faster than Angular in rendrering complex view.\r\n\r\nWith the Microfrontend it's possible the write a parcial of the application with an other Framework/Librery\r\n\r\n![](/images/MF-apps.drawio.png)\r\n\r\n## Agile friendly\r\n\r\nWith Microfrontend technolige each fearture can ben a standalone application that has it's owen develempoent cycle.\r\nSo we can create smaller indepented Teams.\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >\r\n<img src=\"/images/MF1.drawio.png\" />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p >\r\n<img src=\"/images/MF2.drawio.png\" />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n## Indepented deployment\r\n\r\nIn the microfrontend Architecture each feature or module is represented by an indepeneted project, which give us the capability to deploy indepentedly each project wihtout building all projects.\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >\r\n<img src=\"/images/MF3.drawio.png\" />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n## Progressive migration\r\n\r\nLet's say that a company has a 10 years old frontend application written with Angular.js and now they start to migrate to Angular.\r\n\r\nThere's two ways:\r\n\r\nStart an Hybrid project with Angular and Angular.js at the same times, which it's possible and there's many resouces that provide tools and documentaion to accompagne the dev teams to migrate the project, but it's case by case, the project can touch the limit before attending the migration.\r\n\r\nThe other way is to impliment the Microfrontend, buy starting a new projet that mount the older view beside to new ones and write all the new features with new framework, then with a great plan, you can start to migrate securily feature by feature. -->","frontmatter":{"title":"","date":null,"description":null,"categories":null,"cover":null}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/ecmascript/2022/"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}},"next":null},"pageContext":{"id":"f06b9f7a-a50e-51a2-9ed0-83f18fde6d37","previousPostId":"caa9a10e-afc4-5669-87f2-1da44b86a5bb","nextPostId":null,"category":"none"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"]}